<common-name datatype='string'>galR</common-name>
<comment datatype='string'>Based on &lt;i&gt;in vitro&lt;/i&gt; transcription, it was demonstrated that the putative cAMP-CRP-binding site in the galRp promoter region [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8416900&quot;&gt;Weickert93&lt;/a&gt;] is not functional in the purified system [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17630975&quot;&gt;Semsey07&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
Using a library designed to allow for precise control of the concentration of individual transcription factors and transcriptional reporter libraries, Parisutham et al. observed that GalS activates the transcription of &lt;i&gt;galR&lt;/i&gt; [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/35694815&quot;&gt;Parisutham22&lt;/a&gt;]; however, they did not observe an effect of repression by GalS on galR as previously reported by [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17630975&quot;&gt;Semsey07&lt;/a&gt;]. It is not known if there is another DNA-binding site by which GalS activates &lt;i&gt;galR&lt;/i&gt; or if the same DNA-binding site to repress it can also be used to activate it.</comment>
